CALCULATE with filter manipulation:
```dax
// Filter to specific value
Critical Vulns = CALCULATE([Total Vulns], Detections[severity] = 5)

// Remove all filters (% of total)
% of Total = DIVIDE([Total Vulns], CALCULATE([Total Vulns], ALL(Detections)))

// Remove filters except one column (% within category)
% of Category = DIVIDE([Total Vulns], CALCULATE([Total Vulns], ALLEXCEPT(Detections, Detections[category])))

// Activate inactive relationship
By Ship Date = CALCULATE([Total Sales], USERELATIONSHIP(Sales[ShipDate], DateTable[Date]))
```

Conditional logic in DAX:
```dax
// IF for simple branching
Trend Label = IF([MoM Change %] > 0, "Growing", "Declining")

// SWITCH for multi-value branching
Severity Label = SWITCH([severity], 1, "Minimal", 2, "Medium", 3, "Serious", 4, "Critical", 5, "Urgent", "Unknown")

// SWITCH(TRUE()) for range-based logic
Risk Band = SWITCH(TRUE(), [Score] >= 90, "Critical", [Score] >= 70, "High", [Score] >= 40, "Medium", "Low")

// COALESCE for first non-blank
Safe Value = COALESCE([Metric Value], 0)
```
